<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Buhari-ministers-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Buhari, rule of law and fight against corruption" class="amp-wp-295b586"> By Kolawole Olaniyan PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari’s administation’s record on the rule of law is chilling. Since assuming power on May 29, 2015, the president has evinced a stunning disregard for the rule of law and human rights. He has ignored Nigerian judges on at least 40 occasions, and seems to be getting away with it. The fight against corruption has been an important facet of his rhetoric but his persistent disobedience of court orders, disdain for Nigerian judges and flagrant violations of human rights puts into question his commitment to actually ending corruption. Continue reading Buhari, rule of law and fight against corruption at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard